281
00:21:49,010 --> 00:21:50,870
Yes, don't worry.

282
00:21:50,870 --> 00:21:53,560
Ah. You'll have to connect your laptop to the projector with this.

283
00:22:10,130 --> 00:22:14,520
So let's start the meeting on MJ's new song concept.

284
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:16,940
First of all, fashion.

285
00:22:17,760 --> 00:22:20,200
Part-timer, what are you doing?

286
00:22:26,610 --> 00:22:30,550
Is MJ, that scumbag, going to boss you around again today?

287
00:22:30,590 --> 00:22:33,380
I heard he made you signed his signature on many posters on his behalf yesterday too?

288
00:22:33,380 --> 00:22:37,600
Anyway, I'm planning on teaching a lesson.

289
00:22:39,230 --> 00:22:42,230
Are you coming home late today? I have something to show you.

290
00:22:42,230 --> 00:22:45,010
Anyway, call me when you're done.

291
00:22:48,050 --> 00:22:50,460
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

292
00:22:50,460 --> 00:22:53,510
Woo Seung, how could you leave the message window on during the presentation?

293
00:22:53,510 --> 00:22:56,230
- Sign out of it quickly.
- Yes.

294
00:22:57,560 --> 00:23:03,370
So, what is this? She's in a love triangle with Thumbs Up and Slave Underdog.

295
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:07,650
Are they "The Double U Crew"?

296
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:12,250
The Double U Crew. That's funny.

297
00:23:12,250 --> 00:23:15,090
Later, I'll use this as a joke.

298
00:23:15,090 --> 00:23:19,100
The Double U... Crew.

299
00:23:24,040 --> 00:23:28,210
Hey! Why didn't she reply when she read the text messages?

300
00:23:30,620 --> 00:23:32,700
Now, she's ignoring my text messages.

301
00:23:32,700 --> 00:23:35,410
Do you think that will make me give up?

302
00:23:50,640 --> 00:23:55,310
Second Place, do you badmouth me outside the company?

303
00:23:55,380 --> 00:23:59,220
It's not like that.

304
00:24:03,540 --> 00:24:04,740
I'm sorry.

305
00:24:04,740 --> 00:24:08,340
I thought we were like family, but you're nice in front of me,

306
00:24:09,510 --> 00:24:11,880
and you write hateful comments about me behind my back.

307
00:24:11,880 --> 00:24:14,600
Really, I've never written any mean comment.

308
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:18,160
If you're lying about this,

309
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:24,310
you'll be doomed forever from today onward.

310
00:24:25,150 --> 00:24:26,970
I wrote a few times.

311
00:24:29,700 --> 00:24:32,430
I'm going to sleep here, so get out.

312
00:24:32,430 --> 00:24:34,470
Clean things up later.

313
00:24:55,880 --> 00:24:59,010
Choi Woo Seung. Let's talk for a moment.

314
00:24:59,010 --> 00:25:00,790
Didn't I tell you to pretend not to know me at the company?

315
00:25:00,790 --> 00:25:05,000
Forget it. I'll give you a piece of advice so listen carefully.

316
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:09,070
- Lee Ji Hoon and you are never allowed to be together.
- How dare you?

317
00:25:09,110 --> 00:25:13,830
If you were me, and your friend seems to be giving up on being a trainee and now he's going to give up his life too,

318
00:25:13,870 --> 00:25:15,900
- would you be able to stay still?
- What?

319
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:17,910
It seems there are a lot of people and ears here.

320
00:25:17,910 --> 00:25:23,050
A rumor like this... can be really fatal to Ji Hoon.

321
00:25:24,220 --> 00:25:26,510
Follow me to the rooftop.

322
00:25:32,220 --> 00:25:34,600
Hey, seriously!

323
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:43,830
Hey, what's all this?

324
00:25:43,830 --> 00:25:45,520
Why are you home so early?

325
00:25:45,520 --> 00:25:49,980
The meeting ended earlier than expected. But, what is this?

326
00:25:49,980 --> 00:25:53,060
Ta-da! I was going to show you this to surprise you.

327
00:25:53,060 --> 00:25:54,870
You told me you wanted to rest on a hammock.

328
00:25:54,870 --> 00:25:59,010
Well, even if it's not an island, it's just... You can pretend it is. Make yourself feel better.

329
00:25:59,010 --> 00:26:01,450
It was really hard today.

330
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:09,760
"Ji Hoon, I didn't know you'd care about me so much."

331
00:26:09,760 --> 00:26:13,460
"Looking at this hammock, I'm also starting to like you."

332
00:26:14,720 --> 00:26:17,340
You didn't expect this kind of reaction, did you?

333
00:26:17,340 --> 00:26:18,750
Don't even look forward to it.

334
00:26:18,750 --> 00:26:20,230
Not at all.

335
00:26:20,230 --> 00:26:22,570
So, why would you do something you never did?

336
00:26:22,570 --> 00:26:26,020
I already told you. Now I want to express whatever I want to.

337
00:26:27,300 --> 00:26:29,460
- Be honest with me.
- What?

338
00:26:29,460 --> 00:26:34,870
Do you think I don't know you? I'm sure you feel awkward, embarrassed to death to do these kinds of things.

339
00:26:34,870 --> 00:26:36,980
What are you saying? It's not like that.

340
00:26:45,040 --> 00:26:46,940
What is this?

341
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:54,420
How was it? It looked natural, right?

342
00:26:56,560 --> 00:26:58,950
Why are you getting stuff all over your face?

343
00:27:02,670 --> 00:27:05,550
What is this?

344
00:27:07,370 --> 00:27:09,300
- Who is it?
- What?

345
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:11,000
You are not like this at all.

346
00:27:11,040 --> 00:27:15,460
Who taught you this tacky and dirty '90s way of flirting?

347
00:27:15,460 --> 00:27:17,620
It's Thumbs Up, right?

348
00:27:23,550 --> 00:27:26,030
It's awkward to do this and you've just started.

349
00:27:26,030 --> 00:27:29,400
It's so awkward and embarrassing that it's driving me crazy.

350
00:27:30,710 --> 00:27:34,610
Can't we just go back to being friends like our old days?

351
00:27:34,610 --> 00:27:37,790
I don't know if it's convenient for you, but I don't want to!

352
00:27:39,140 --> 00:27:40,670
What should I do?

353
00:27:40,670 --> 00:27:44,020
Anyway, I made a hammock for you so try it out.

354
00:27:44,020 --> 00:27:46,130
So, who told you to make this?

355
00:27:46,130 --> 00:27:48,760
First, lie down. Get up.

356
00:27:50,970 --> 00:27:52,670
Here.

357
00:27:54,030 --> 00:27:56,630
♫ I like it when you look at me from by my side ♫

358
00:27:56,630 --> 00:28:00,280
That's it. That's why I'm telling you to not overdo it. Just do what you normally do.

359
00:28:00,280 --> 00:28:03,060
What do you mean to not overdo it?

360
00:28:03,060 --> 00:28:04,370
My bag.

361
00:28:04,380 --> 00:28:09,240
♫ Remember my love, my eyes, my story ♫

362
00:28:09,270 --> 00:28:15,170
Oh! This is really comfortable. So comfortable. It's my first time lying in a hammock.

363
00:28:15,170 --> 00:28:16,410
♫  I only love you ♫

364
00:28:16,410 --> 00:28:19,100
I'll bring some more fruit. Wait a moment.

365
00:28:19,100 --> 00:28:21,640
♫ Oh, oh, oh. Yeah! ♫

366
00:28:21,690 --> 00:28:24,410
♫ Listening to you as you’re in my arms ♫

367
00:28:24,410 --> 00:28:27,030
